com.misc.common.moplaf.time.continuous

Interface Distribution

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator.ObjectWithPropagatorFunctionAdapter
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DistributionImpl

    public interface Distribution
extends com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator.ObjectWithPropagatorFunctionAdapter
    A Distribution implements a generalized function of time (java Date). The function is piecewise linear. The Distribution nor its slope are continuous. For every time t, the value of the function (its amount) as well as its slope are maintained before and after any time.

    A Distribution receives

    • EventsProviders through the relation #eventsProviders
    • child Distributions through the relation #childDistribution

    The Distribution

    • considers the events
      • StartEvent and EndEvent
      • provided by the EventsProviders
      • belonging to the child Distributions
    • selects the considered events in the horizon
    • sorts the selected events
    • publishes the resulting sets of events
      • in the relation DistributionImpl#sequenceEvents
      • in the attribute DistributionEventImpl.eventNr
      • in the references DistributionEventImpl.next and DistributionEventImpl.previous
    • maintains the value and slope of the distribution at every event
      • in the attribute DistributionEventImpl.amountBefore
      • in the attribute DistributionEventImpl.amountAfter
      • in the attribute DistributionEventImpl.slopeBefore
      • in the attribute DistributionEventImpl.slopeAfter

    The following features are supported:

    • Time Unit
    • Horizon Start
    • Horizon End
    • Child Events
    • Sequence Events
    • Start
    • End
    • Events Providers
    • Parent Distribution
    • Child Distribution
    • Provided Events
    See Also:
    ContinuousPackage.getDistribution()

      • getEarliestBelow

        java.util.Date getEarliestBelow(java.util.Date after,
                              float duration,
                              float amount)
        Returns the earliest moment after the moment after when the distribution is at least amount for the given duration.

        The returned earliestMoment satisfies: for every moment between earliestMoment and earliestMoment + duration, we have: amount is below this.getAmount(moment).

        Parameters:
        after - the moment after which capacity must be available
        duration - the duration for of the required capacity
        amount - the amount of the required capacity
        Returns:
        earliest moment when the required capacity is available

      • getEarliestOutputPossible

        java.util.Date getEarliestOutputPossible(float above,
                                       java.util.Date after,
                                       float duration,
                                       float amount)
        Return the earliest moment when it is possible to produce continuously a quantity amount during duration while staying under this Distribution and above a minimum amount above.

        Say rate is amount / duration. Then the returned earliestMoment satisfies: for every moment between earliestMoment and earliestMoment + duration, we have: above + moment * rate is below this.getAmount(moment).

        Parameters:
        above - the minimal amount that may not be used
        after - the moment after which production must start
        duration - the duration for the production
        amount - the amount to produce
        Returns:
        earliest moment when possible to produce
